        "timestamp": "2021-09-27 13:14:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> I'm not sure about commenting out....Let's see what the other committers think.\n\nI think one of java processes could run in the foreground, and in that case I think there would be no need for ngnix.    But let me ask you, is there a review though in OOM subsystem for gui?  I was just looking and see no gui component chart.   If that's the case, *no* OOM work for GUI just usage in docker/docker-compose, I am ok with the way that you had it initially (as we wouldn't break requirements).   As a note, the GUI port should also be configurable at a later point at least when an OOM chart is done for it.",
